From: Antony Vance <antony.vance@ni.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Feb 2016 01:18:05 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] opencv : Download ippicv from NI server

CMake is not able to download ippicv package from sourceforge https server due to disabled openssl option. This breaks opencv build with download hash mismatch error.
This change downloads ippicv pacakge from NI http server  to avoid build error.

Signed-off-by: Antony Vance <antony.vance@ni.com>
---
 3rdparty/ippicv/downloader.cmake | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/3rdparty/ippicv/downloader.cmake b/3rdparty/ippicv/downloader.cmake
index f25e5cc..bc32ff8 100644
--- a/3rdparty/ippicv/downloader.cmake
+++ b/3rdparty/ippicv/downloader.cmake
@@ -62,7 +62,7 @@ function(_icv_downloader)
       if(DEFINED ENV{OPENCV_ICV_URL})
         set(OPENCV_ICV_URL $ENV{OPENCV_ICV_URL})
       else()
-        set(OPENCV_ICV_URL "http://sourceforge.net/projects/opencvlibrary/files/3rdparty/ippicv")
+        set(OPENCV_ICV_URL "http://download.ni.com/ni-linux-rt/src/")
       endif()
     endif()
 
